nodes.title: CONTINIOUS GENERATION
widgets_values:
You can copy/paste as many I2V parts as you want. To get a continous output simply connect last image of the previous node to start image of next node.

Don't forget to connect Filename of last I2V node to Final Save.

You can also use extra load image nodes to set start/end of certain parts if you like.

nodes.title: WHERE TO PICK MODELS?
widgets_values:
Model, CLIP and VAE selection nodes are in a subgraph named "Loader_T2V" and "Loader_I2V" inside T2V and First I2V subgraphs.

- Changes inside "Loader_T2V" only affect T2V subgraph.
- Changes inside "Loader_I2V" affect all I2V subgraphs.
- Changes inside "ksampler_x3",  affect both T2V and I2V.

You can toggle upscale and interpolation on/off in this subgraph.

Final output gets saved under output folder.

nodes.title: T2V ON/OFF
widgets_values: To disable T2V entirely, you might want to save a copy of the workflow where you've deleted it until there's a stable bypass system for subgraphs.

nodes.title: NO LORA PASS
widgets_values: Number of no lightx2v passes are told to improve motion quality. If you want to skip this phase make sure to set the no_lora_steps to 0 and enable add_noise in "Ksampler - high"

nodes.title: VAE Decode
widgets_values: You should only switch to tiled decode if you get OOM to get least artifacts. If it still happens then decrease values down slightly and carefuly as it tends to cause more artifacts.

nodes.title: Removed Global Seed
widgets_values:
Removed global noise seed, if you want to repeat a previous generation just right click on it from the history and load workflow, change the parameters you want and it will continue generation from there.

You can save the related workflow to regenerate in future sessions.

nodes.title: Clip
widgets_values: Clip loader with GGUF support. Can load .safetensor files as well. You can switch to default clip loader if you get any errors.

nodes.title: Custom Lora
widgets_values: You can set and extend your custom loras inside this subgraph. These will affect every I2V part

nodes.title: Speed Optimizations
widgets_values: You can toggle sageattention/torch compile nodes if you cant get them to work but it will take longer to generate videos.

nodes.title: Models
widgets_values: Switch between GGUF/Load Diffusion Loader if you want.

nodes.title: UPSCALE
widgets_values:
Enable upscale subgraph to upscale generated videos using model. You can scale down the final output using post scale down.

INCREASES GENERATION TIME SIGNIFICANTLY

Or you can just connect input and output of upscale image by for simple resize. May not increase quality as much but it's way faster.

nodes.title: INTERPOLATION
widgets_values:
Enable RIFE VFI node in this subgraph if you want to interpolate the video generated.

Change multiplier value to determine number of frames generated.

x2 is 30fps
x4 is 60fps

INCREASES GENERATION TIME SIGNIFICANTLY

nodes.title: SAMPLER
widgets_values: To change sampling settings you can modify this subgraph. Steps per each one of high/low passes is already exposed to outer scope.

nodes.title: LATENT
widgets_values: You can edit output resolution and length (must be 1) for T2V output here

nodes.title: MODEL
widgets_values: You can edit T2V models inside this subgraph for all T2V parts
